    "from coolbox.api import *"

  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "encouraging-milton",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "bedpe_path = \"../../../tests/test_data/bedpe_var_chr9_4000000_6000000.bedpe\"\n",
    "cool_path = \"../../../tests/test_data/cool_chr9_4000000_6000000.mcool\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "practical-inquiry",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Open region"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "copyrighted-negative",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The \"open_region\" parameter control the behavior of contact fetching. If specified to False, will only fetch the contacts which it's double sides located in the region."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "partial-snowboard",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "nbsphinx-thumbnail"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1133.86x198.425 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "arc = Arcs(bedpe_path, open_region=False) + TrackHeight(5)\n",
    "frame = XAxis() + arc\n",
    "\n",
    "frame.plot(\"chr9:4500000-6000000\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bulgarian-roommate",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Otherwise(default), will fetch the contacts only one side located in the region:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "varying-underground",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "nbsphinx-thumbnail"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1133.86x198.425 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "arc = Arcs(bedpe_path, open_region=True) + TrackHeight(5)\n",
    "frame = XAxis() + arc\n",
    "\n",
    "frame.plot(\"chr9:4500000-6000000\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "printable-blanket",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Line width"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "satisfied-fiber",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "`Arcs` will calculate the line width according to the contacts score specifed in BEDPE file. When you use Pairs file or scores are not provided in BEDPE, score will set to `1`. \n",
    "\n",
    "The default width calculation equation is: `0.5 + math.sqrt(score)` You can change it with `score_to_width` parameter:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "described-poverty",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1133.86x198.425 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "arc = Arcs(bedpe_path, score_to_width=\"0.5 + np.log(score)\") + TrackHeight(5)\n",
    "frame = XAxis() + arc\n",
    "\n",
    "frame.plot(\"chr9:4500000-6000000\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "supposed-discharge",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "If the static line width is needed, use the `line_width` parameter:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "pleasant-progress",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1133.86x198.425 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "arc = Arcs(bedpe_path, line_width=2) + TrackHeight(5)\n",
    "frame = XAxis() + arc\n",
    "\n",
    "frame.plot(\"chr9:4500000-6000000\")"
   ]
  }
